”I’m getting some money for my unemployment benefits, but it’s nothing compared to what the stimulus check would’ve been,” Sherman told me.
Many are saying that any monetary support — either to a dependent or their parent — would be better than none, regardless of a dependent’s age.
The $1,200 check would’ve helped a lot, she said, since she’s now pulling from her savings to pay any bills.
The young adults I spoke to wanted to dispel the myth that all dependents, specifically college students, are privileged and have their education and expenses paid for — a stereotype that is clearly false.
Those who became financially independent in 2020, however, will eventually receive the stimulus money they’re owed in 2021 if they file their 2020 tax return, Maag said.